Wednesday 1 October 2008 will be recorded in the history of Pra<0xC5><0xBE>sk<0xC3><0xBD> Dopravn<0xC3><0xAD> podnik (the Prague Transport Agency) as the date when the first passengers will get on the metro, trams and buses, who, instead of having a paper ticket, will have in their pocket an electronic coupon.
