Namely in the peri-urban trains and bus lines 300 to 499, which are mainly used by the inhabitants of the municipalities of Central Bohemia to access the capital.
"In the trains integrated in Pra<0xC5><0xBE>ská integrovaná doprava (integrated transports of Prague), the controllers are equipped with card readers, with the help of which they establish the temporary and zonal validity of the coupons;" explained the control of the tickets Filip Drapal of the organization Ropid, which designs the schedules of transports in Prague commun.
The peri-urban buses are equipped with card readers integrated into the driver’s cash register.
When boarding it is therefore necessary not only to show the smart card to the driver, but also to place the Opencard in the place indicated on the side of the checkout.
