The issuers of zealous invoices also did not inquire about Budapest travel agencies, which were part of their choice, but only organized trips abroad. Thus, naively, they indicated stays in Hungary on invoices to be paid in cash, which also goes against the accounting practices of the agency.
In addition, as was shown during the investigation, they also added VAT on these documents, while services relating to travel activities, the destination of which is located outside the European Union, are charged without VAT.
