The Prosecutor's investigation reveals that the "issuers" also made mistakes in mentioning as a service the carriage of goods by road, which the issuing company of the invoices could not exercise, since its profile was investment advice.
In addition, it is also for defects of form, such as inappropriate types of invoices and false stamps, that the invoices issued to the order of Együtt to Harmadik <0xC3><0x89>vezredért Alap<0xC3><0xAD>tvány, of XXI. Századi Kulturális Egyesület and Biztos Pont turned out to be false.
Just as in the case of the Ravenna Bt. company or the Kunfehértó sports internship, both of which deny being the authors of the invoices issued on their behalf.
The counterfeiters also failed to pay attention to the fact that the company HIB Kft., established in Ny<0xC3><0xAD>regyháza, was in liquidation at the time (in 2001) the Fiatal Városért Egyesület group was supposed to have a meal at their home.
Deliberately Established Invoices
Another category of invoice issuers is those who were fully aware that they were required to issue fictitious invoices.
The Esély Budapestért Alap<0xC3><0xAD>tvány Foundation, at the request of the Fiatal Baloldal - Ifj<0xC3><0xBA> Szocialisták group, has prepared an invoice to the order of the Együtt Foundation in Harmadik <0xC3><0x89>vezredért, for a sum of four million HUF.
