Open Office, this is the third edition of the "anti-Microsoft" package
OpenOffice.org.3.0, the open source suite of personal productivity that aims to reach more and more users, from home to office, from professionals to public administration, offering a free alternative to the most famous Microsoft Office.
After almost a year of work, carried out by volunteer developers, monitored by SUN Microsystem, the new Open Office package is shown to the general public with various novelties: from the welcome screen, and the revised and less austere interface, to other more important ones, such as the compatibility born for the latest Apple Mac OS X operating system, and the support for the new ISO Format, ODF (O Open Document).
Open Office paid particular attention to the interaction with the Office 2007 suite, and it is indeed possible to open documents with the new Microsoft extension (.docx, .xlsx, .pptx.)
Also interesting are some features specific to some modules, such as the one that allows to reduce the dimensions of PowerPoint presentations, useful for example, to send them by e-mail, or to import PDF files into the graphic design module, keeping the original appearance of the page.
Always on this front, it is possible to create "Hybrid PDF" documents that unite the typical graphic of the Adobe format with the elements of a spreadsheet or a text maker.
Collaboration between multiple people is an element that has had various improvements within the applications: in the spreadsheet, various users can intervene, avoiding conflicts about changes, in the development of texts, because each collaborator is assigned a color of comments for better recognition in the revision phase.
Some companies are even working to bring certain OpenOffice features to the web (on the cloud, on the cloud), and in the coming weeks, they are expected to issue the final result.
The Italian version can be downloaded at http://it.openoffice.org/download/3.0.0/download300.htmlet and is in addition to the English version that was on the mirror since Friday.
In addition to Windows and Mac OS, the suite is as usual also available for the Linux operating system.
On request, the installation cd can be shipped home or to the workplace.
And if the theme of free can be a way to spread it in homes, it is precisely in the business, that Open Office the suite tries the great challenge, can already count on various projects carried out in the public administration and schools.
Not to mention the realities that offer a service of training, consultation and assistance, ideal for small and medium-sized companies, which could also open up to business prospects.
Open Office consists of five main modules: Writer, for the video writing equivalent of Word; Calc, is the spreadsheet that aims to replace Excel; Impress, for the rival PowerPoint presentations; Dbase, such as the famous Access, is the program that allows to work on databases; finally Drwa is the graphical module.
Goal for 2008 to reach 5 million downloads, and considering that today there are almost 3 million and 600 miles, it is likely that with the release of the new version, we can even exceed the expected figure
